snippet.textDisplay:
Don’t forget tatum is putting up these numbers while playing in a system that shares rhe ball and has 3 other 20 point scorers around him that need their shots. Also, don’t forget that the celtics only lost by 2, with some terrible possibly game costing calls, on the road IN LA, without their 5 time all star 22 ppg scoring veteran leader point guard Kemba walker playing a single minute, as well as Hayward and brown being subpar compared to what they’ve been recently, outside of some late clutch plays. Yes the loss is frustrating, but, even as someone who is a lakers fan as well, I think if you are being objective, this game only proved once again that the Celtics are the better basketball team, especially when healthy.
Boston has had such a good season this year and they’ve barley had a chance to play with their desired starting 5 all sharing the court. When they have know, the numbers show how scary they can be. I think Boston has a chance to really make some noise come playoff time. If they can get to the playoffs in full healthy though, with Robert Williams as well, I honestly think they have a chance to win the title. I’m not sure how they would get past the bucks, but, we all saw what that Milwaukee juggernaut looked like in the playoffs last year compared to the reg, plus we saw what little progress Giannis has made( if any) when it comes to 2 elite teams battling out a close game in the finals minutes last week in the all star game, so anything is possible. IF Boston can get to the finals, weirdly enough, I think they march up better against the clippers and lakers than they do against some of the eastern teams. I guess we will see!! But it’s SO clear at this point that this group of celtics does so much better being overlooked than they do under the spotlight
